Class LocationSerializer

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.onarandombox.multiverseinventories.share.LocationSerializer
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    SharableSerializer<org.bukkit.Location>
    @Deprecated
public final class LocationSerializer
extends java.lang.Object
implements SharableSerializer<org.bukkit.Location>
    Deprecated.
    Locations no longer need a special serializer because they are ConfigurationSerializable. This remains to convert legacy data.
    A simple SharableSerializer usable with Location which converts the Location to the string format that is used by default in Multiverse-Inventories.

        This deserializes the data for a Sharable. You must be expecting the type of data coming in in order to process this. That type will generally be the type that this serializes as with SharableSerializer.serialize(Object).

      • serialize

        public java.lang.Object serialize​(org.bukkit.Location location)
        Deprecated.
        Description copied from interface: SharableSerializer
        This serializes the data for a Sharable. The output is an Object but what you return is up to you, however, this is limited by the constraints of the persistence method. Generally, returning a String is the safest way to serialize your data. Most boxed primitives are accepted as well as Lists of boxed primitives and Map<String, Object>.
        Specified by:
        serialize in interface SharableSerializer<org.bukkit.Location>
        Parameters:
        location - The value of the data represented by the Sharable.
        Returns:
        The serialized form of the data.
